<div class="ip-event-info">
  <h2 id="title">Welcome to the Intercom Party 2016 Ember App</h2>

  Use the links below to get started:
  <section>
    <aside>What is it?</aside>
    <article>{{#link-to "about"}}About{{/link-to}}</article>
  </section>
  <section>
    <aside>Who can attend?</aside>
    <article>Anyone within 100km of head office</article>
  </section>
</div>


Click this button to attempt to load customer data from JSON locally and see the Mirage Load conflict in the console-
<button type="button" name="button" {{action 'loadCustomerData'}}>Load JSON</button>

<div class="ip-customer-table">
  <h2 id="title">Customers Attending 2016</h2>
    <table>
      <thead class="ip-customer-table-heading">
        <tr>
          <th>ID</th>
          <th>Customer ID</th>
          <th>Customer</th>
          <th>Longitude</th>
          <th>Latitude</th>
          <th>Distance Away</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="ip-customer-table-body">
          {{#each model as |customerInstance|}}
            {{customer-information customer=customerInstance distance="100"}}
          {{/each}}
      </tbody>
    </table>

</div>
